Package com.itsradiix.discordwebhook.embed

Class Embed

java.lang.Object
com.itsradiix.discordwebhook.embed.Embed
public class Embed
extends java.lang.Object
The Embed class represents an Embedded Message that can be send with a DiscordWebHook message. The Class has an internal Builder Class to easily instantiate an Object. Make sure to read the wiki page on our GitHub to understand how to use this effectively. https://github.com/ItsRadiiX/Definity-Webhooks/wiki

  • Constructor Details

    • Embed

      private Embed​(java.lang.String title, java.lang.String description, java.lang.String url, int color, java.lang.String timestamp, Footer footer, Thumbnail thumbnail, Image image, Author author, java.util.List<Field> fields)
      Private default Constructor for instantiating an Embed Object.
      Parameters:
      title - Title of the embedded message.
      description - Description of the embedded message.
      url - URL of the Title (If clicked).
      color - Color of the Border of the embedded message.
      timestamp - LocalDateTime to String, this will be displayed in the footer of the embedded message.
      footer - Footer Object of the embedded message.
      thumbnail - Thumbnail Object of the embedded message.
      image - Image Object of the embedded message.
      author - Author Object of the embedded message.
      fields - List of fields of the embedded message.

    • Embed

      public Embed()
      This allows you to create an Embed without using the Builder class. (Not recommended)
